<dashboard version="1.1">
  <label>Overview</label>
  <description>Welcome to the Canadian Centre for Cyber Security Alerts Monitor with MITRE ATT&amp;CK Intelligence</description>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <html>
        <div style="padding: 20px;">
          <h1 style="color: #1E88E5;">🇨🇦 Canadian Center for Cyber Security Alert Monitor</h1>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">
            This app automatically collects and monitors security alerts from the Canadian Centre for Cyber Security (CCCS) 
            with <strong>automated MITRE ATT&amp;CK threat intelligence enrichment</strong>.
          </p>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 30px;">Available Dashboards</h2>
          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
            <div style="padding: 15px; background-color: #E8F5E9; border-left: 4px solid #4CAF50;">
              <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">CCCS Alerts Dashboard</h3>
              <p style="font-size: 13px;">Traditional alert monitoring with visualizations, vendor filtering, and critical alerts table.</p>
              <a href="cccs_dashboard" style="color: #2E7D32; font-weight: bold;">View Dashboard →</a>
            </div>
            <div style="padding: 15px; background-color: #FCE4EC; border-left: 4px solid #E91E63;">
              <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">MITRE ATT&amp;CK Analysis</h3>
              <p style="font-size: 13px;">Threat intelligence dashboard with technique mapping, threat scores, and tactical analysis.</p>
              <a href="mitre_dashboard" style="color: #C2185B; font-weight: bold;">View Dashboard →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <h2 style="margin-top: 30px;">Quick Start</h2>
          <ul style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8;">
            <li>
              <strong>View Alerts:</strong> Click on "CCCS Alerts" in the navigation above</li>
            <li>
              <strong>MITRE Intelligence:</strong> Click on "MITRE ATT&amp;CK Analysis" for threat analysis</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Search Alerts:</strong> Use the search: <code>index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts</code>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Data Collection:</strong> Runs automatically every 15 minutes</li>
            <li>
              <strong>First Collection:</strong> Wait 15 minutes after installation for data to appear</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2 style="margin-top: 30px;">Core Features</h2>
          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 10px;">
            <div>
              <h3 style="color: #1976D2;">Data Collection</h3>
              <ul style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8;">
                <li>Automated CCCS alert collection</li>
                <li>Dual-layer deduplication system</li>
                <li>Smart change detection with hashing</li>
                <li>Dedicated index: <code>cyber_gc_ca</code>
                </li>
                <li>CVE extraction and parsing</li>
                <li>Active exploit detection</li>
                <li>Affected products identification</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 style="color: #C62828;">MITRE ATT&amp;CK Enrichment</h3>
              <ul style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8;">
                <li>Automatic technique mapping (185+)</li>
                <li>Threat score calculation (0-100)</li>
                <li>Tactical classification (14 tactics)</li>
                <li>Attack complexity analysis</li>
                <li>Critical technique alerting</li>
                <li>Severity classification</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div style="margin-top: 30px; padding: 20px; background-color: #FFF3E0; border-left: 4px solid #FF9800;">
            <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Advanced Deduplication System</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6;">
              This app uses a dual-layer validation system to prevent duplicate events:
            </p>
            <ul style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.8;">
              <li>
                <strong>Layer 1 - Feed Hash:</strong> Checks if the entire CCCS feed has changed (fast exit if no changes)</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Layer 2 - Event Hash:</strong> Validates each individual event JSON to prevent duplicates</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Hash Storage:</strong> JSON file with timestamps for tracking (<code>cccs_event_hashes.json</code>)</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Auto-Cleanup:</strong> Automatically removes event hashes older than 31 days</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Smart Detection:</strong> Even if CCCS republishes alerts, they won't be duplicated in Splunk</li>
            </ul>

          </div>
          
          <h2 style="margin-top: 30px;">Data Source</h2>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6;">
            <strong>Organization:</strong> Canadian Centre for Cyber Security (CCCS)<br/>
            <strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.cyber.gc.ca/" target="_blank">cyber.gc.ca</a>
            <br/>
            <strong>Feed Type:</strong> Atom XML with MITRE enrichment<br/>
            <strong>Update Frequency:</strong> Real-time (checked every 15 minutes)<br/>
            <strong>MITRE Framework:</strong> <a href="https://attack.mitre.org/" target="_blank">ATT&amp;CK Enterprise Matrix</a>
          </p>
          
          <div style="margin-top: 40px; padding: 20px; background-color: #E3F2FD; border-left: 4px solid #1E88E5;">
            <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Quick Search Examples</h3>
            <pre style="background: white; padding: 10px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 12px;">
# All alerts
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts

# Critical MITRE severity alerts
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts mitre_severity=critical

# High threat score alerts (≥70)
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts mitre_threat_score&gt;=70

# Specific MITRE technique (e.g., T1190 - Exploit Public-Facing)
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts mitre_techniques{}.id="T1190"

# Alerts by MITRE tactic
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts mitre_tactics{}="Initial Access"

# Active exploits with MITRE mapping
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts exploit_mentioned=true mitre_enriched=true

# Cisco advisories
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts alert_title="*Cisco*"

# Recent alerts (last 24 hours)
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts earliest=-24h
            </pre>
          </div>
          
          <div style="margin-top: 30px; padding: 20px; background-color: #F3E5F5; border-left: 4px solid #9C27B0;">
            <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Pre-configured Alerts</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 14px;">This app includes 7 automated alerts for critical threats:</p>
            <ul style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.8;">
              <li>
                <strong>Critical MITRE Techniques:</strong> T1190, T1068, T1486, T1003, T1078</li>
              <li>
                <strong>High Threat Score:</strong> Alerts with score ≥ 70</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Active Exploits:</strong> Vulnerabilities being exploited in the wild</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Initial Access Surge:</strong> Spike above 7-day average</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Ransomware Detection:</strong> T1486 technique alerts</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Lateral Movement:</strong> Network propagation techniques</li>
              <li>
                <strong>Daily Summary:</strong> Morning intelligence briefing</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="font-size: 13px; margin-top: 15px;">
              <strong>Enable alerts:</strong> Settings → Searches, reports, and alerts → Filter by "Canadian Cyber Centre"
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div style="margin-top: 30px; text-align: center;">
            <a href="mitre_dashboard" style="display: inline-block; padding: 15px 30px; background-color: #D32F2F; color: white; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; margin: 10px;">
              MITRE ATT&amp;CK Dashboard
            </a>
            <a href="cccs_dashboard" style="display: inline-block; padding: 15px 30px; background-color: #1E88E5; color: white; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; margin: 10px;">
              CCCS Alerts Dashboard
            </a>
          </div>
          
          <h2 style="margin-top: 40px;">Documentation</h2>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6;">
            <strong>Complete Guide:</strong> See README.md in <code>$SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/cccs_alerts_app/</code>
            <br/>
            <strong>Release Notes:</strong> See RELEASE_NOTES.md for version history<br/>
          </p>
          
          <p style="margin-top: 40px; font-size: 12px; color: #666; text-align: center;">
            Version 3.1.0 with Advanced Deduplication System | December 2025<br/>
            Developed by Alexandre Argeris
          </p>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <single>
        <title>Total Alerts Collected</title>
        <search>
          <query>
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts 
| stats count
          </query>
          <earliest>0</earliest>
          <latest>now</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="colorMode">block</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x65A637","0x6DB7C6","0xF7BC38"]</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[0,100]</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <single>
        <title>MITRE Enriched Alerts</title>
        <search>
          <query>
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts mitre_enriched=true
| stats count
          </query>
          <earliest>0</earliest>
          <latest>now</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="colorMode">block</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x65A637","0x6DB7C6","0xF7BC38"]</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <single>
        <title>Unique MITRE Techniques</title>
        <search>
          <query>
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts mitre_techniques{}.id=*
| stats dc(mitre_techniques{}.id) as count
          </query>
          <earliest>0</earliest>
          <latest>now</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="colorMode">block</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x65A637","0x6DB7C6","0xF7BC38","0xF58F39"]</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <single>
        <title>Critical Severity (MITRE)</title>
        <search>
          <query>
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts mitre_severity=critical
| stats count
          </query>
          <earliest>0</earliest>
          <latest>now</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="colorMode">block</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x65A637","0xF7BC38","0xF58F39","0xD93F3C"]</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[0,5,10]</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <single>
        <title>Average Threat Score</title>
        <search>
          <query>
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts mitre_threat_score=*
| stats avg(mitre_threat_score) as avg_score
| eval avg_score=round(avg_score,1)
          </query>
          <earliest>0</earliest>
          <latest>now</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="colorMode">block</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x65A637","0x6DB7C6","0xF7BC38","0xF58F39","0xD93F3C"]</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[0,30,50,70]</option>
        <option name="numberPrecision">0</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <single>
        <title>New Alerts (Last 24h)</title>
        <search>
          <query>
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts earliest=-24h
| stats count
          </query>
          <earliest>-24h</earliest>
          <latest>now</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="colorMode">block</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <single>
        <title>Active Exploits Detected</title>
        <search>
          <query>
index=cyber_gc_ca sourcetype=cccs:alerts exploit_mentioned=true
| stats count
          </query>
          <earliest>0</earliest>
          <latest>now</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="colorMode">block</option>
        <option name="useColors">1</option>
        <option name="rangeColors">["0x65A637","0xF7BC38","0xD93F3C"]</option>
        <option name="rangeValues">[0,5]</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <single>
        <title>Data Collection Status</title>
        <search>
          <query>index=cyber_gc_ca | stats count | eval status=if(count&gt;0, "Active", "Not working")
| fields status</query>
          <earliest>-24h@h</earliest>
          <latest>now</latest>
        </search>
        <option name="colorMode">block</option>
        <option name="drilldown">none</option>
        <option name="refresh.display">progressbar</option>
      </single>
    </panel>
  </row>
</dashboard>